---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import aboutImage from '~/assets/images/Sunset.jpg';
const metadata = {
  title: 'About - Travel Chronicles Studio',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>

  <!-- HERO IMAGE -->
<section class="relative w-full h-[60vh]">
  <Image
    src={aboutImage}
    alt="Sunset travel scene"
    class="w-full h-full object-cover"
    loading="eager"
  />

  <!-- optional cinematic overlay -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/20"></div>
</section>

  <!-- ABOUT CONTENT -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">

    <p>
      We’re a husband and wife team with a shared obsession: finding the next horizon.
    </p>

    <p>
      Not the whip-cracking, temple-dodging kind of explorers… more the “early morning coffee in a new city,
      maps open, camera charged, and curiosity leading the way” kind.
    </p>

    <p>
      From ancient streets echoing with history to quiet corners most people walk straight past, we travel like
      modern-day adventurers—always chasing stories, light, and moments that feel just a little bit larger than life.
    </p>

    <p>
      We get lost often (on purpose… mostly), and somehow that’s where the best discoveries tend to happen—usually
      followed by pastry and espresso.
    </p>

    <p>
      For us, travel isn’t about ticking places off a list—it’s about collecting the feeling of being somewhere new, together.
    </p>

    <p>
      And if there’s a little adventure along the way? Even better.
    </p>

  </section>

</Layout>